oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Fearless Five Fathers at Graduation
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lewis, Victoria J.
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The “Fearless Five,” Peggy Barfield (Atchison), Dottie Bryant (McGahagin), Vicki Lewis (Woodward), Jean Lloyd (Berry), and Jeanne Eyman (Smith) became friends soon after their arrival at the Florida State College for Women in 1940. They were known as a daring, lively, fun loving group with little regard for strict campus rules. They were all P.E. majors, and after graduation in 1944, went on to successful careers in education.

Personal photographs of Florida State College for Women student Victoria J. Lewis, class of 1944 (BS, Education). These photographs are a part of the Victoria J. Lewis Scrapbook, 1940-1944 (Accession No. HP-2007-079). Special thanks to Bert Page for identifying persons in this photograph. B/W.

oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Fearless Five Mothers with Diplomas
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lewis, Victoria J.
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The “Fearless Five,” Peggy Barfield (Atchison), Dottie Bryant (McGahagin), Vicki Lewis (Woodward), Jean Lloyd (Berry), and Jeanne Eyman (Smith) became friends soon after their arrival at the Florida State College for Women in 1940. They were known as a daring, lively, fun loving group with little regard for strict campus rules. They were all P.E. majors, and after graduation in 1944, went on to successful careers in education.

Personal photographs of Florida State College for Women student Victoria J. Lewis, class of 1944 (BS, Education). These photographs are a part of the Victoria J. Lewis Scrapbook, 1940-1944 (Accession No. HP-2007-079). Special thanks to Bert Page for identifying persons in this photograph. B/W.

oai_dc:dc.dc:title: "Mister" Elliot
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Cooper, Jewell Genevieve
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: According to a newspaper clipping next to the photograph, "Mister" Jules Elliot was the night watchman at FSCW who became "somwhat of a character at the college". Very knowledgeable about the campus, Elliot apparently maintained a radio set within the administration building (Westcott). The article notes, "One of the mysteries of the college is just when 'Mister' Elliot sleeps. At almost any hour of the day, and at almost any place, he may be seen downtown."

oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Dr. Ralph L. Eyman, Peggy Barfield, Jean Lloyd, Dorothy B. McGahagin, Victoria Lewis, and Jeanne Eyman (the Fearless Five) at Graduation
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lewis, Victoria J.
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Heritage Protocol, Florida State University, Tallahassee, Florida.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The “Fearless Five,” Peggy Barfield (Atchison), Dottie Bryant (McGahagin), Vicki Lewis (Woodward), Jean Lloyd (Berry), and Jeanne Eyman (Smith) became friends soon after their arrival at the Florida State College for Women in 1940. They were known as a daring, lively, fun loving group with little regard for strict campus rules. They were all P.E. majors, and after graduation in 1944, went on to successful careers in education.

Personal photographs of Florida State College for Women student Victoria J. Lewis, class of 1944 (BS, Education). These photographs are a part of the Victoria J. Lewis Scrapbook, 1940-1944 (Accession No. HP-2007-079). Special thanks to Bert Page for identifying persons in this photograph. B/W.
